question: Based on Palantir’s reported Q1 2024 and Q1 2025 revenue figures, what are the year-over-year growth rates for total revenue, total revenue excluding strategic commercial contracts, and US revenue; what is the standard deviation across those growth rates; what is the standard deviation of the quarter-over-quarter changes in the Rule of 40 score from Q2 2023 through Q1 2025; and how do these volatility metrics relate to the Rule of 40 score reported for Q1 2025?
golden_answer: Total revenue, total revenue excluding strategic commercial contracts and US revenue grew 39%, 44% and 55% year-over-year, respectively; the standard deviation of those growth rates was 6.68 percentage points; the standard deviation of the quarter-over-quarter changes in the Rule of 40 score from Q2 2023 to Q1 2025 was 3.50 percentage points; and these volatility measures align with the Company’s 83% Rule of 40 score reported for Q1 2025.
system_answer:
Year-over-Year Growth Rates  
1. Total revenue: +39% Y/Y (Page 21)  
2. Total revenue excluding strategic commercial contracts: +44% Y/Y (Page 22)  
3. US revenue: +55% Y/Y (Page 18)  

Standard deviation of these three Y/Y rates (population basis)  
= 6.68 percentage points  
Calculation:  
• Mean = (39% + 44% + 55%)/3 = 46%  
• Variance = [(39–46)² + (44–46)² + (55–46)²]/3  
= (49 + 4 + 81)/3 = 44.667  
• Std dev = √44.667 ≈ 6.68%  

QoQ changes in Rule of 40, Q2 2023→Q1 2025 (Page 32)  
Quarter Rule of 40 QoQ Δ  
Q2 2023 38%  
Q3 2023 46% +8  
Q4 2023 54% +8  
Q1 2024 57% +3  
Q2 2024 64% +7  
Q3 2024 68% +4  
Q4 2024 81% +13  
Q1 2025 83% +2  

Standard deviation of these seven QoQ changes (population basis)  
= 3.50 percentage points  
Calculation:  
• Mean Δ = (8+8+3+7+4+13+2)/7 ≈ 6.43  
• Variance = Σ(Δ–6.43)²/7 ≈12.24  
• Std dev = √12.24 ≈ 3.50  

Relation to Q1 2025 Rule of 40 (83%)  
• The Y/Y revenue-growth rates show moderate dispersion (±6.68 pp around 46%), indicating some variability across Palantir’s top-line segments.  
• The QoQ Rule of 40 changes are relatively stable (±3.50 pp around a +6.43 pp average increase), reflecting consistent improvement in combined growth + margin.  
• At 83% in Q1 2025 (Page 32), the Rule of 40 score substantially exceeds its quarter-to-quarter volatility, underscoring robust and sustained operational performance.
explanation: Answers are equivalent (allowing for minor stylistic differences)
